For more details, see the paper "Testing Static Analysis Tools Using
Exploitable Overflows From Open Source Code", Misha Zitser, Richard Lippmann,
and Tim Leek.

COMPILING
make clean
make

RUNNING TEST CASES
run with:       sig-bad
result:         cp1 gets overflowed in rrextract and a segmentation fault occurs when memcpy gets a negative 3rd argument.  
